Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes a heuristic algorithm for computing a partial dense cover of a graph, which involves optimization and computational complexity, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.SD (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions benchmarking techniques and evaluation metrics, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
